{# ── FAQ ── #}
<section class="section section--dark">
  <div class="container--narrow">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <span class="section-label">Questions</span>
      <h2>Website FAQs</h2>
    </div>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">How much does a site cost?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Pricing depends on scope — a simple artist site with EPK and tour dates is priced differently than a full site with merch integration, email capture, and custom animations. We scope every project individually and put a fixed price in writing before anything starts. Reach out for a quote.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">Will I be able to update it myself?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Yes — that's a priority. We build sites that can be updated without a developer. Tour dates, bio updates, new music links, merch items — all manageable through a simple content file or a CMS if needed. We document everything at handoff.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">Do you build on Squarespace or WordPress?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>We don't. Squarespace and WordPress carry monthly platform fees and performance limitations that custom-built sites don't. Our stack — Eleventy on GitHub Pages — is faster, cheaper to maintain, and doesn't lock you into a subscription to keep the lights on.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">What if I already have a domain?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>No problem — we connect to your existing domain. Just need access to your DNS settings, which we walk you through if you haven't done it before.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">Do you offer ongoing maintenance?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Yes — a monthly maintenance option is available for artists who want someone else handling updates, security, and integrations on an ongoing basis. We quote this separately from the initial build.</p></div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

